{Speech 5 Answer 16}{}{Something from childhood}
{Speech 6}{}{Rumors reached us that, even though we took the half-dead Patriarch prisoner, the Hubologists replicated him anyway. Knowing that such a thing is strictly forbidden, we tried to find out how it was possible. The truth that surfaced shocked even us. We never imagined the churchmen would turn out to be such hypocrites. The Hubologists needed "special" material for their research, and they agreed to replicate the Patriarch in exchange for a dozen children no older than 10. Naturally, the churchmen, who masturbate so fervently over that vile old man, agreed to it, forgetting all about their principles. Beasts. Just like us. Although our plan to remove the Patriarch from the world didn't work, it warms the heart to know that the old man who now preaches in Klamath is not the real one. We have the original. And tomorrow a lobotomy and an anal trepanation await him.\n}
{Speech 6 Answer 18}{}{…added much later…}
{Speech 7}{}{A big black cannon, just like my first machine gun. It spins, it whirs, it brings death. The trader was torn apart in seconds, he never even understood what happened, he was literally cut in two by such a wild stream of bullets. His guards, worthless guards, good for nothing, slow to react. Some of them just stood there - stunned, they had never seen guts before. Without lifting my finger off the trigger I began to sweep the barrel from one guard to the next. One man's arm, twirling in funny pirouettes, came off his body, he squealed like a pig and dropped. Another man's right side turned into bloody chunks, and after that everything was a haze, screams and howls, they spun and writhed, and when I ran out of bullets, I started clubbing them with the 24-kilogram barrel, so hard to kill that way. Looks like someone over there is still twitching.\n\nVasya. Machine Gun Vasya.}
{Speech 7 Answer 5}{}{Back.}
{Speech 8}{}{Fucking brahmins opens up a huge field for the imagination. For instance, you can chop off one head and fuck the windpipe, and it'll still moo! \nFolk wisdom.}
{Speech 8 Answer 5}{}{Back.}
{Speech 9}{}{      ...below us is a long, gentle slope, set with enormous gray-black stone faces - erosion-eaten statues, carved and erected here by a civilization long gone. Now we are at the top, and there is nowhere left to retreat. Behind our backs, to the east, a sheer cliff dropped to the ocean once called the Pacific. And to the west lay the slope with the stone faces and the screaming, advancing men of the Paladin. We killed three of their squads, but by the most modest count, two dozen are still alive. Twenty men, mouths gaping, faces painted blue, one with a gauss rifle, some even with a bazooka... against six of us...\n}
{Speech 9 Answer 22}{}{Next}
{Speech 10}{}{Note: this message, wrapped in a condom, was extracted from brahmin dung. Apparently it ate one of the prisoners, swallowing the note hidden in his backside.\n\nMy name is Victor. I am 31 years old. I lived in the city of Broken Hills. I took any work I could get, even shoveling brahmin shit. I have no family, my parents died when I was still a teenager. A lousy life, but what's happening now is far worse.}
{Speech 10 Answer 24}{}{Next}
{Speech 11}{}{We slept on the bare floor, they fed us scraps. After a couple of days they dragged Bill off somewhere. Bill was one of the big shots in BH. I heard no screams, at first I thought they were interrogating him. But as it turned out, I heard no screams because the walls were soundproofed. They injected Bill with some drug that was supposed to completely remove sensitivity to pain. They sat him on a chair, tied him down, and tore out his right canine tooth with rusty pliers. The drug didn't work, Bill howled in pain. The doctors decided to tear out the left canine too. Bill thrashed, spat blood. They injected him with something again. As it turned out, there were several samples of the drug. With some strange device, like garden shears, they cut off the index finger of his right hand. The drug didn't work. Bill screamed and cried, and these monsters cut off his little finger too. }
{Speech 11 Answer 12}{}{Next}
{Speech 12}{}{ They came for Sebastian. He sold armor, weapons, ammo in BH. A great guy, full of cheer. I wonder what's happening to him. A couple of hours have passed already. Bill said he heard the doctors saying they needed to watch what happens to the heart while the drug is administered. I think they want to see how the drug wears out the heart, since they clearly don't want to risk the health of their own fighters. They brought Sebastian back. He lies in his cell in a pool of blood. He's dead. I wonder what happened. Maybe his heart gave out, though more likely they never even intended to bring him back to his senses. }
{Speech 12 Answer 13}{}{Next}
{Speech 13}{}{Another day has passed, Bill is dead. Sebastian has been lying there a long time. Nobody even thinks of taking away the corpses. The smell is awful. Two fighters came in, from their conversation I gathered one of them is called Chuvachello, what nonsense, I wonder what that name means. They told us that today there would be some event in the sanctuary and that we would take part. I wonder what role is in store for us. I've heard they sometimes hold ritual sacrifices. Just imagining it makes my blood run cold. They'll wash us and dress us up. A few hours left to wait. What a nightmare, I've just come back from the event. My last cellmate, Mark Wahlberg, is gone. He was sacrificed to some deity, I don't even remember which. They laid him on some slab and tied him down. They blindfolded him. Cthulha recited either a prayer or just some verse, in a language I didn't understand. }
{Speech 13 Answer 14}{}{Next}
{Speech 14}{}{They opened the veins on both his arms, blood poured into vessels. Mark didn't scream and lay completely silent, maybe they injected him with that drug, though I doubt it, these people are devoid of any humanity, I think Mark simply endured. When the blood stopped flowing, they lifted the vessels and poured Mark's blood over his head, doused him with some liquid, probably flamethrower fuel, and set him alight. Mark screamed. I wonder why burn someone alive at all, it's just awful. Nothing was left of Mark. }
{Speech 14 Answer 25}{}{Next}
{Speech 15}{}{Bullets bounced off the titanium skeleton one after another. Their ultra-powerful gauss rifles were no greater threat to the terminator than a mosquito bite is to a man. The pathetic alliance freaks strained to knock out my eyes, to crack my skull… They knew nothing of the Hubologists' new technology. When, retreating, they found themselves at a dead end and saw up close the gleaming metal showing where chunks of flesh had been torn away, the realization dawned on them, but it was too late...  The rifle barrels slid tightly into their anuses, and in that moment they cursed themselves for not taking pistols instead of rifles.\n}
{Speech 15 Answer 5}{}{Back.}
{Speech 16}{}{I remember little of my childhood. No parents, living in the church of some shithole town that isn't even on the map. The forever-stoned priest mumbles from morning till night about damn roots and flowers, groping the other children's backsides at every chance. He's afraid to come near me, he remembers how he lost the tip of a finger.\n}
{Speech 16 Answer 17}{}{Next.}
{Speech 17}{}{I remember a day when the sun shone especially bright on me. I waited until the little pup, Robko, everyone's favorite, went into the outhouse, then slipped in after him. One blow of a rock to the head was enough to send his body tumbling head-first into the gaping hole that led down to an ocean of shit. They searched for him for three days, relieving themselves onto his body without suspecting a thing… That was my first murder… Defecating on corpses came to seem especially appealing to me, remembering that blond-haired boy.}
{Speech 17 Answer 5}{}{To the main menu.}
{Speech 18}{}{After the Patriarch's mysterious disappearance, this question intrigued us once more. It turned out that behind the words "he has departed this mortal world" lay a cruel truth: the Patriarch was shot in the back by none other than Fargus, his loyal deputy. But he can be understood: as a result of the replication, the Patriarch's personality was crippled, since full replication is impossible while the original is alive. Over time the clone showed more and more signs of madness and, in the end, became a threat to the church. }
{Speech 18 Answer 21}{}{Next}
{Speech 19}{}{However, for some time the Patriarch's clone remained alive - he was kept in secret chambers beneath the temple, in the hope of finding a way to restore his sanity. But over time the cult of veneration of the "holy" Patriarch spread so widely that it became pointless to "bring him back to life." So the decision was made to be rid of him.}
{Speech 19 Answer 20}{}{Next}
{Speech 20}{}{For this purpose, a freshly minted knight of the round table, Boxifag, was assigned to the direct executor - Fargus. The young knight could not bear the display of such sacrilege, and as a result he suffered a nervous breakdown and began to hear voices. \nAfter that he was expelled from the knights and placed in a monastery in order to "cast out the demons that had possessed him," which constantly whispered to him the words "BLOOD," "GUTS," "SHIT." There he stayed until the monastery was discovered during one of our raids. Boxifag understood whose voices he had been hearing all this time, and gladly joined the Zerg.}
{Speech 20 Answer 5}{}{To the main menu.}
{Speech 21}{}{Moreover, it turned out that just before replication the Hubologists copy all the parameters of the one being replicated using their secret technology. Ideally - at the moment of death. But since the Patriarch was at this base when the clone was created, the clone inherited the consequences of all the experiments we performed on the "original." When the Patriarch, during a service in Klamath, began shouting "BLOOD GUTS SHIT!" before the townsfolk - the churchmen understood that the time had come to act.}
{Speech 21 Answer 19}{}{Next}
{Speech 22}{}{          - Yes! Yes, very good. Everyone to me! Zergs, to me! To me, I say!\n          - As for the Zergs, here I am. And we are the last.\n          - Good. We attack them. Spare no one.\n          - No, spare no one, absolutely no one.\n          - And we will not accept their surrender, if they try to give up.\n          - Never. Even if all twenty raise their hands.\n          - And now, my friends... For the Zerg!\n          }
{Speech 22 Answer 23}{}{Next}
{Speech 23}{}{- For the Zerg! - six voices cry out beneath the scorching sun. This is their death, the death of the brave, the death of everything, but it no longer troubles them. The familiar red fury, comparable only to madness, veiling the mind, drowns out every thought.\n          - To me! - shouts Cthulha, - Forward! For the Zerg!\n          - For the Zerg! - repeats FORevenge behind his back. In one hand, raised to the sky, he holds someone's guts, with the other he steadies his beloved vindicator.\n          - Take no prisoners! - shouts Chuvachello, - TAKE NO PRISONERS!.. \n\nA tale from life.}
{Speech 23 Answer 5}{}{To the main menu}
{Speech 24}{}{Our city survived many attacks by bandit gangs. But on May 15, 2242, the city was subjected to a massive assault. The bandits, they call themselves "Zerg," arrived on some contraption, killed almost all the city's inhabitants, carried off everything of value, and took me and three other people with them. I thought they wanted to kill us on the way, but I was wrong. They dragged us into some cave, somewhere in the mountains. They distributed us among cells, it reeked worse than stagnant brahmin shit. That same day their doctor examined us. The bandits drank, smoked, shot up, fucked all day, mostly with whores, but there were also those who did it with brahmins. Total psychos. Among them was the gang's leader, everyone called him Cthulha. How I want to slit his throat. }
{Speech 24 Answer 11}{}{Next}
{Speech 25}{}{As for me, I played the role of a servant. Fetch this, carry that. Good thing they didn't touch me. It's pleasant, after all, to find myself back in a cell. I want to sleep, want it badly. At night they brought some Fargus into the cell. He said there had recently been a raid on Klamath, almost everyone was killed, a few people, including him, were taken prisoner. They're being interrogated right now. The soldier who brought Fargus in said that in the morning they would lead me off somewhere. I wonder what they want to do with me... I think this is my last entry in the diary...}
{Speech 25 Answer 5}{}{To the main menu.}
